HEADWORD: All Fools Day
<hw>All" Fools' Day`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <def>The first day of April, a
day on which sportive impositions are practiced.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The first of April, some do say,⟦br⟧
Is set apart for <qex>All Fools' Day</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Poor Robin's
Almanack (1760).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

